    <body>
      <div xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113">
        <head xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-Hd1e105">Quaestio 51</head>
        <head xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-Hd1e108" type="question-title">
          <supplied>Utrum doctrina <name>Venerabilis Anselmi</name> rationabiliter debeat reprobari?</supplied>
        </head>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e111">
          Utrum doctrina 
          <name ref="#Anselm">Venerabilis Anselmi</name> 
          rationabiliter debeat reprobari?
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e122">
          Quod sic, 
          <app>
            <lem>arguitur</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>
          quia est erronea, 
          ut patet 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e125">
            8 
            <title>De libero arbitrio</title>
          </ref>,
          ubi docet quod rectitudinem voluntatis 
          Deus non potest auferre a voluntate, 
          et tamen tenet 
          quod illa est alia res a voluntate, 
          quod est erroneum 
          quia omnem rem distinctam totaliter 
          ab alia potest Deus separare, 
          <app>
            <lem>ergo</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          etc.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e132">
          Dicitur quod distinguitur a voluntate.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e138">
          Contra aut ergo est effective a voluntate vel non, 
          si sic, 
          contra, 
          non est in potestate voluntatis causare 
          in se rectitudinem sed servare, ut dicit. 
          <!-- break ?? -->
          Etiam affectiones creatae sunt 
          <app>
            <lem>a</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">in</rdg>
          </app> 
          Deo 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e156">
            <title>De concordia</title>, 
            capitulo 17
          </ref>, 
          ergo etc.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e163">
          <pb ed="#P" n="160-v"/>
          <cb ed="#P" n="a"/>
          <app>
            <lem>Similiter</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">Similificat</rdg>
          </app> 
          <app>
            <lem>si causat</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          rectitudinem aut volendo aut non. 
          Si volendo 
          et nullus vult rectitudinem 
          nisi habens rectitudinem, 
          ergo prius habet quam causet, 
          et haec 
          <app>
            <lem>est</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          ratio eiusdem 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e204">
            <title>De concordia</title>,
            capitulo 13
          </ref>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e211">
          Si rectitudo non est effective a voluntate, 
          ergo non est imputandum libero arbitrio, 
          <app>
            <lem>quod est</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          contra 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e213">
            <name>Augustinum</name>, 
            primo 
            <title>Retractionum</title>,
            <app>
              <lem>nono capitulo</lem>
              <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-inversion">capitulo nono</rdg>
            </app>  
          </ref>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e223">
          <app>
            <lem>Dicitur</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">Dicit</rdg>
          </app> 
          quod dependet a voluntate 
          quantum conservationem, 
          non quantum ad productionem.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e243">
          Contra, 
          in potestate peccatorum est producere 
          <app>
            <lem n="producere"/>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-present">
              contra
            </rdg>
          </app>
          contritionem, 
          et omnis contritio est rectitudo voluntatis, 
          ergo etc. 
          Confirmatur 
          quia rectitudo voluntatis est 
          <app>
            <lem n="est"/>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-present">
              eam
            </rdg>
          </app>
          velle 
          quod Deus vult eam velle 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e261">
            <title>De libero arbitrio</title>, 
            capitulo 8
            <!--
              ("velle quod deus vult eam" this phrase is found directly 
              in Holcot, Sent. I, q. 3, see 
              http://thesis-project.ro/robertusholcot/files/Circa%201um%20librum%20Sententiarum%2C%20q.%203.pdf, 
              (folio 185a), 
              but is also there associated with De libertate arbitrii, c. 8.,
            --> 
          </ref>,
          sed
          tale velle est effective 
          a voluntate, ergo etc.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e195">
          Item, 
          omne, 
          quod homo habet 
          si 
          <app>
            <lem>illud vult</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-inversion">vult illud</rdg>
          </app> 
          habere et non habet nisi 
          <app>
            <lem>illud velit</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-inversion">velit illud</rdg>
            
          </app> 
          habere, 
          habet a voluntate, 
          ut videtur. 
          Rectitudo est 
          <app>
            <lem>huiusmodi</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P">huius</rdg>
          </app>, 
          igitur
          etc.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e207">
          Item, 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e302">
            II <title>Cur Deus homo</title>, 
            capitulo 14
          </ref> 
          ponit 5 propositiones. 
          Prima est 
          <app>
            <lem>quod</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          facere contra Dei voluntatem, 
          <app>
            <lem>etiam</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">in</rdg>
          </app> 
          quod putamus laevissimum mortale, 
          est tantae gravitatis quod fieri non 
          <app>
            <lem>deberet</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">deberent</rdg>
          </app> 
          pro infinitis mundis 
          <app>
            <lem>salvandis</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">salandis</rdg>
          </app>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e344">
          Sed contra, 
          tunc quodlibet peccatum est 
          infinitae malitiae intentione 
          quia, 
          si 
          <app>
            <lem>finitae</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">infinitae</rdg>
          </app>, 
          tunc solo 
          <app>
            <lem>aliquorum</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">aliquod</rdg>
          </app> 
          <app>
            <lem>mundorum</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">mondorum</rdg>
          </app> 
          <app>
            <lem>foret</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">esset</rdg>
          </app> 
          ita bona, 
          sicut illud foret malum.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e239">
          Secunda propositio,
          <app>
            <lem>quod</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          minima laesio Christi 
          <app>
            <lem>est</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P">esset</rdg>
          </app> 
          <app>
            <lem>maius</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          malum
          <app>
            <lem n="malum"/>
            <rdg wit="#B">infinitum</rdg>
          </app>
          quam omnia peccata 
          extra personam Christi.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e419">
          Contra, 
          tunc interfectio Christi non 
          <app>
            <lem>fuisset</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">fuit</rdg>
          </app> 
          magis mala 
          quam minima laesio 
          <app>
            <lem>Christi</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e251">
          Tertia, 
          vita Christi fuit magis bona 
          quam omnia peccata sunt mala.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e442">
          Contra, 
          tunc fuit magis bona quam
          <app>
            <lem n="quam"/>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-present" cause="repetitio">quam</rdg>
          </app>
          eius interemptio. 
          Consequens contra eum 
          quia 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Qd1e454" source="http://scta.info/resource/u8ue3d-d1e494">
              omne bonum 
              tam bonum est 
              quam mala est destructio
            </quote>
            <bibl>
              <name>Anselmus</name>
              <title>Cur Deus Homo</title>
              II, c. 14
              (XXX) <!-- schmidt , p. 114 ?? -->
            </bibl>
          </cit>,
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e452" corresp="#beq3sc-d1e113-Qd1e454">
            <app>
              <lem>II</lem>
              <rdg wit="#B" type="correction-addition">
                <add>II</add>
              </rdg>
            </app> 
            <title>Cur Deus homo</title>, 
            capitulo 14
          </ref>,
          et tam malum fuit eum occidere 
          quam 
          <app>
            <lem>bona</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">bonam</rdg>
          </app> 
          fuit eius 
          <app>
            <lem>vita</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">vitam</rdg>
          </app>
          <app>
            <lem n="vitam"/>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-present">capitulo iii</rdg>
          </app>. 
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e275">
          Item, 
          vita Christi fuit sufficiens satisfactio pro peccato, 
          ergo fuit bonum infinitum. 
          Consequentia probatur per 
          <app>
            <lem>illud</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">aliud</rdg>
          </app> 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e470" corresp="#beq3sc-d1e113-Qd1e478">
            I
            <title>Cur Deus homo</title>, 
            capitulo 21
          </ref> 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Qd1e478" source="http://scta.info/resource/u8ue3d-d1e287">
              numquam satisfacis 
              nisi reddas aliquid 
              <app>
                <lem>maius</lem>
                <rdg wit="#B">magis</rdg>
              </app> 
              quam 
              <app>
                <lem>sit</lem>
                <rdg wit="#B">si</rdg>
              </app> 
              illud pro quo 
              <app>
                <lem>peccatum facere</lem>
                <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-inversion">
                  facere peccatum
                </rdg>
              </app> 
              non debueras
            </quote>
            <bibl>
              <name>Anselmus</name>, 
              <title>Cur Deus Homo</title>,
              I, c. 21 
              (XXX) <!-- schmidt, p. 89?? -->
            </bibl>
          </cit>. 
          Sed pro nullo bono finito deberet homo peccare, 
          ut dicit prima propositio, 
          ergo 
          <app>
            <lem>etc.</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e299">
          Quarta 
          <app>
            <lem>propositio</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Qd1e559" source="http://scta.info/resource/u8ue3d-d1e494">
              omne bonum tam bonum 
              est quam 
              <app>
                <lem>mala</lem>
                <rdg wit="#B">malum</rdg> <!-- dbcheck -->
              </app> 
              est eius destructio
            </quote>
            <bibl>
              <name>Anselmus</name>
              <title>Cur Deus homo</title>
              II, c. 14
              (XXX) <!-- schmidt , p. 114 ?? -->
            </bibl>
          </cit>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e309">
          Contra, 
          praecipiat 
          Deus <name>Sorti</name> 
          quod non destruat istam festucam 
          sub pena peccati mortalis, 
          et quod non occidat 
          leonem sub pena peccati venialis, 
          et faciat contra utrumque, 
          tunc festuca est maioris bonitatis quam leo 
          quia eius destructio est peior.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e326">
          Quinta, 
          vita corporis 
          Christi est magis amabilis 
          quam omnia 
          <app>
            <lem n="omnia"/>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-present">eius</rdg>
          </app>
          <app>
            <lem>peccata</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">peccato</rdg>
          </app> sunt odibilia.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e620">
          Contra, 
          tantum 
          <app>
            <lem>primae</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">primo</rdg>
          </app> 
          est amabilis, 
          <app>
            <lem>est</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">et</rdg>
          </app> 
          aequa 
          quia, 
          amando Deum odit peccatum, 
          et odiendo peccatum, 
          amat Deum. 
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e340">
          Item, 
          si sic et constat quod nullus 
          <app>
            <lem>debuit</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">debuisse</rdg>
          </app> 
          eum plus 
          <app>
            <lem>
              amasse 
              quam ipse se amavit 
              ergo ille debuit eum plus
            </lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent" cause="homoteleuton"/>
          </app> 
          amasse 
          quam odisse peccatum, 
          ergo non debuit 
          <app>
            <lem>illam vitam</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-inversion">vitam illam</rdg>
          </app> 
          dedisse pro satisfactione peccati.
        </p> 
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e354">
          Item, 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e673">
            <title>Proslogion</title>, 
            capitulo 25
          </ref> 
          <app>
            <lem n="25"/>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-present">nota</rdg>
          </app>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e363">
          Item, 
          dicit de <name>Beata Virgine</name> quod 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Qd1e692" source="http://scta.info/resource/u8ue3d-d1e516" type="paraphrase">
              fuit concepta et nata in originali 
              <app>
                <lem>peccato</lem>
                <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
              </app>
            </quote>
            <bibl>
              <name>Anselmus</name>,
              <title>Cur Deus Homo</title>,
              II, c. 16
              (XXX) <!-- schmidt, p. 116 ?? -->
            </bibl>
          </cit>, 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e705" corresp="#beq3sc-d1e113-Qd1e692">
            2o <title>cur deus homo</title> capitulo 16
          </ref>.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-d1e712">
          Item,
          probat quod Deus non potest 
          tollere rectitudinem a voluntate 
          quia vel volendo vel 
          <app>
            <lem>nolendo</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>.
          Non 
          <app>
            <lem>nolendo</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">volendo</rdg>
          </app>, 
          ut patet. 
          Nec volendo 
          quia, 
          si sic, 
          <app>
            <lem>vult</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">vel</rdg>
          </app> 
          quod 
          <app>
            <lem>faciat</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">facit</rdg>
          </app>, 
          et a cuius voluntate 
          vult auferre rectitudinem, 
          non vult eam servare rectitudinem. 
          Sed servare rectitudinem est velle 
          <app>
            <lem>sicut</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">quod</rdg>
          </app> 
          Deus vult 
          <app>
            <lem>eam</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">eum</rdg>
          </app> 
          velle, 
          ergo si Deus rectitudinem tollit a voluntate, 
          non vult 
          <app>
            <lem>eam</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">eum</rdg>
          </app> 
          velle quod vult 
          <app>
            <lem>eam</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">eum</rdg>
          </app> 
          velle. 
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e387">
          Sed contra 
          <app>
            <lem>hoc</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>, 
          quia diabolus 
          <app>
            <lem>vult</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          sicut Deus vult eum velle 
          quia Deus 
          <app>
            <lem>scit</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">sit</rdg>
          </app> 
          consequentiam
          <app>
            <lem n="consequentiam"/>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-present">istam</rdg>
          </app>
          esse bonam, 
          diabolus est obstinatus in malo, 
          igitur vult iniuste, 
          et Deus vult antecedens, 
          et consequentiam esse bonam, 
          igitur 
          <app>
            <lem>sequitur quod</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          vult consequens. 
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e401">
          Item, 
          si nulla voluntas foret 
          <cb ed="#P" n="b"/>
          recta nisi 
          quia vellet 
          sicut Deus vult eam velle, 
          sequitur quod in <name>Christo</name> fuisset aliqua 
          <app>
            <lem>voluntas</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          non recta 
          <app>
            <lem>quando</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B">cum</rdg>
          </app> 
          dixit 
          <ref xml:id="beq3sc-d1e113-Rd1e862" corresp="#beq3sc-d1e1134-Qd1e412">
            <title>Matthaeo</title> 26
          </ref> 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-Qd1e412" ana="#mt26_39">
              non sicut ego volo, 
              <app>
                <lem>sed sicut tu</lem>
                <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
              </app>
            </quote>
            <bibl>
              <title>Matthaeus</title>
              26:39
            </bibl>
          </cit> 
          etc. 
        </p>
        <p xml:id="beq3sc-d1e1134-d1e421">
          Item, 
          contra illam 
          formam 
          <app>
            <lem>arguendi</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          <name>Anselmi</name> 
          <app>
            <lem>arguit sic</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>, 
          quia quando Deus aufert gratiam, 
          aut vult eum non habere gratiam aut non vult. 
          Si vult eum non
          <app>
            <lem>non</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>, 
          <app>
            <lem>etc.</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>
          igitur etc., 
          pro tunc non est debitor gratiae.
          <app>
            <lem>Sed</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          contra, praecipit ei semper habere gratiam, 
          <app>
            <lem>igitur</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>.
          Si vult eam habere, 
          igitur 
          <app>
            <lem>non</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          aufert.
        </p>
        <p>
          Ad illam 
          propositionem 
          <app>
            <lem>igitur</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app> 
          de rectitudine voluntatis, 
          <app>
            <lem>dico quod</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>
          intelligit quod Deus 
          non potest 
          <app>
            <lem>illam separare</lem>
            <rdg wit="#B" type="variation-inversion">separare illam</rdg>
          </app> 
          a voluntate habente gratiam <unclear>ipsa invita</unclear> 
          de potentia ordinata.
          <app>
            <lem>Et sic patet finis quaestionis</lem>
            <rdg wit="#P" type="variation-absent"/>
          </app>.
        </p>
      </div>
